00016 /*                                                                          */
00017 /*                                                                          */
00018 /*     Given a latitude and a longitude this subroutine looks up the        */
00019 /*     geographical region number as defined by Edward A. Flinn and         */
00020 /*     Eric R. Engdahl in Reviews of Geophysics Vol.3 No.1 pp.123-149       */
00021 /*     Feb.1965 and in the Bulletin of the Seismological Society of         */
00022 /*     America Vol.14 No.3-Part II pp.771-992 Jun.1974.                     */
00023 /*     Also included are four additional geographical regions as agreed     */
00024 /*     at IUGG in August 1987, six additional regions approved at IASPEI    */
00025 /*     in August 1989, a further eighteen regions presented at IUGG in      */
00026 /*     August 1991, and all finally approved at IUGG in July 1995.          */
00027 /*                                                                          */
00028 /*                                                                          */
00029 /*     and given the latitude                                               */
00030 /*          and the longitude                                               */
00031 /*     the program looks up the geographical region , and                   */
00032 /*                          also the seismic region.                        */
00033 /*                                                                          */
00034 /*     Note:  No test is made for a latitude and longitude near a           */
00035 /*     boundary; the nearest integer value is used.                         */
00036 /*                                                                          */
00037 /*                                                                          */
00038 /*     The world is segmentised by Flinn and Engdahl as follows -           */
00039 /*                                                                          */
00040 /*                                     Y.N                                  */
00041 /*                                      .                                   */
00042 /*                                      .                                   */
00043 /*                           NW  ***    .    ***  NE                        */
00044 /*                               *2*    .    *1*                            */
00045 /*                           +-  ***    .    ***  ++                        */
00046 /*                                      .                                   */
00047 /*                                      .                                   */
00048 /*                         Quad 2       .       Quad 1                      */
00049 /*                                      .                                   */
00050 /*                  W                   .                    E              */
00051 /*                  ..........................................              */
00052 /*                  X                   .                    X              */
00053 /*                                      .                                   */
00054 /*                         Quad 3       .       Quad 4                      */
00055 /*                                      .                                   */
00056 /*                                      .                                   */
00057 /*                           SW  ***    .    ***  SE                        */
00058 /*                               *3*    .    *4*                            */
